I need to also add a CSS rule to handle the hover state for the entire card when it contains a link. Actually, looking at the existing CSS, I can see there's already a `.card:has(a)` selector that applies hover effects. This should work with the updated HTML since the cards now contain anchor tags that wrap the content.

The CSS already has:
```css
.card:has(a) {
  cursor: pointer;
}
.card:has(a):hover {
  transform: translateY(-6px);
  box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(56,189,248,0.15);
}
```

This should already handle the hover effects for the entire card. Let me verify that the change is complete.

